  "notes": "Complete official FIFA World Cup 2026 group draw (drawn 5 Dec 2025, Washington D.C.). Verified: 12 groups (A-L) x 4 teams = 48 teams total. Team assignments are consistent across the Wikipedia 2026 FIFA World Cup draw article, the main 2026 FIFA World Cup article, the Group A article, and multiple news sources (NBC, ESPN, Sky Sports).\n\nPlayoff qualifiers (all confirmed and correctly placed): UEFA play-off winners = Bosnia and Herzegovina (BIH, Group B; beat Italy on penalties), Czechia (CZE, Group A), Sweden (SWE, Group F), Türkiye (TUR, Group D). Inter-confederation play-off winners = Iraq (IRQ, Group I) and DR Congo (COD, Group K). Italy did NOT qualify.\n\nFIFA 3-letter codes: those for the host nations / Pot-1 seeds (MEX, CAN, USA, BRA, GER, NED, BEL, ESP, FRA, ARG, POR, ENG) are standard, long-established FIFA codes. All other codes were verified against Wikipedia's List of FIFA country codes. Notable/easily-confused codes confirmed: South Africa=RSA, South Korea (Korea Republic)=KOR, Czechia=CZE, Curaçao=CUW, Côte d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast)=CIV, Cabo Verde (Cape Verde)=CPV, DR Congo=COD, Saudi Arabia=KSA, Switzerland=SUI, Türkiye=TUR, Algeria=ALG (FIFA uses ALG, not ALG's ISO 'DZA').\n\nNaming notes: Group A team 4 is listed by FIFA/Wikipedia as \"Czechia\" (formerly Czech Republic); Group D team 4 as \"Türkiye\" (Turkey); Group E as \"Côte d'Ivoire\" (Ivory Coast) and \"Curaçao\"; Group H as \"Cabo Verde\" (Cape Verde). All names/codes refer to the same teams.\n\nWithin-group order above reflects pot order where available (Pot 1 listed first); FIFA's official standings ordering would reflect live results, which were not used for the draw composition.",
